      <akn:section eId="sec_8_2010">
        <akn:num>8-2010</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Sick or injured horses.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_8-2010_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The owner, operator, or custodian of a horse engaged in the horse-drawn carriage trade that is in pain, sick, diseased, lame, or injured shall take action to obtain immediate veterinary treatment, care, and attention for the horse.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_8-2010_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>An injured, sick, diseased, or lame horse shall not be sold or otherwise disposed of except in a humane manner.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_8-2010_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>No person shall drive, use, or work an injured, sick, diseased, or lame horse in the horse-drawn carriage trade.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
